Tap Edit medical info in the options menu
Medical information is only shown if you show your name and picture

ICE is an internationally widespread function for reaching relatives or friends in case of an emergency. It is intended for emergency personnel and will be found in the emergency dialer if the phone is locked.
ICE is the internationally known short form for In Case of Emergency. It can give emergency personnel quick access to important medical information about you.

In the ICE information, you can enter your medical status, such as allergies and medications you are using, and contact information to your closest relatives or friends. The ICE information can be accessed from the lock screen even if the phone is locked.
Note that your name must be added in the Myself information in order to enter medical information.
Medical information can give emergency personnel quick access to your medical needs or illnesses.
Note that the medical information you enter can be accessed even if the device is locked.
Note: This status is not legally binding, just a hint in case of emergency. To be legally binding, it is necessary to follow the existing guidelines for donor registration in your country.
